      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@MatthewRead Due to erasure, the actual type cannot be checked at runtime by Mockito.  So you can&#39;t even use <code>isA()</code>.  If the object holds a <code>Class</code> object corresponding to the type, and the interface exposes this, I guess you could check it in a custom matcher.  Or for example in case of a <code>Collection</code> you could check the type of the elements."
